      • id

        @JsonPropertyDescription(value="An identifier for this particular release of information. A release identifier must be unique within the scope of its related contracting process (defined by a common ocid), and unique within any release package it appears in. A release identifier must not contain the # character.")
private java.lang.String id
        Release ID

        An identifier for this particular release of information. A release identifier must be unique within the scope of its related contracting process (defined by a common ocid), and unique within any release package it appears in. A release identifier must not contain the # character. (Required)

      • ocid

        @JsonPropertyDescription(value="A globally unique identifier for this Open Contracting Process. Composed of a publisher prefix and an identifier for the contracting process. For more information see the [Open Contracting Identifier guidance](http://standard.open-contracting.org/latest/en/schema/identifiers/)")
private java.lang.String ocid
        Open Contracting ID

        A globally unique identifier for this Open Contracting Process. Composed of a publisher prefix and an identifier for the contracting process. For more information see the [Open Contracting Identifier guidance] (http://standard.open-contracting.org/latest/en/schema/identifiers/) (Required)

        Release Tag

      • initiationType

        @JsonPropertyDescription(value="String specifying the type of initiation process used for this contract, taken from the [initiationType](http://standard.open-contracting.org/latest/en/schema/codelists/#initiation-type) codelist. Currently only tender is supported.")
private Release.InitiationType initiationType
        Initiation type

        String specifying the type of initiation process used for this contract, taken from the [initiationType] (http://standard.open-contracting.org/latest/en/schema/codelists/#initiation-type) codelist. Currently only tender is supported. (Required)

      • parties

        @JsonPropertyDescription(value="Information on the parties (organizations, economic operators and other participants) who are involved in the contracting process and their roles, e.g. buyer, procuring entity, supplier etc. Organization references elsewhere in the schema are used to refer back to this entries in this list.")
private java.util.Set<Organization> parties
        Parties

        Information on the parties (organizations, economic operators and other participants) who are involved in the contracting process and their roles, e.g. buyer, procuring entity, supplier etc. Organization references elsewhere in the schema are used to refer back to this entries in this list.

      • language

        @JsonPropertyDescription(value="Specifies the default language of the data using either two-letter [ISO639-1](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes), or extended [BCP47 language tags](http://www.w3.org/International/articles/language-tags/). The use of lowercase two-letter codes from [ISO639-1] (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes) is strongly recommended.

      • relatedProcesses

        @JsonPropertyDescription(value="If this process follows on from one or more prior process, represented under a separate open contracting identifier (ocid) then details of the related process can be provided here. This is commonly used to relate mini-competitions to their parent frameworks, full tenders to a pre-qualification phase, or individual tenders to a broad planning process.")
private java.util.Set<RelatedProcess> relatedProcesses
        Related processes

        If this process follows on from one or more prior process, represented under a separate open contracting identifier (ocid) then details of the related process can be provided here. This is commonly used to relate mini-competitions to their parent frameworks, full tenders to a pre-qualification phase, or individual tenders to a broad planning process.

      • getRelatedProcesses

        public java.util.Set<RelatedProcess> getRelatedProcesses()
        Related processes

        If this process follows on from one or more prior process, represented under a separate open contracting identifier (ocid) then details of the related process can be provided here. This is commonly used to relate mini-competitions to their parent frameworks, full tenders to a pre-qualification phase, or individual tenders to a broad planning process.
